summary: This is an email chain from July 2019 between FBI personnel and Assistant U.S. Attorneys regarding the shipping of approximately 23 boxes of case records from two FBI case files (72-MM-113327 and 31E-MM-108062) related to an investigation. The emails coordinate logistics and confirm the prosecutors' contact information.

keyFacts: The document references the transfer of approximately 23 boxes of case records from two specific FBI case files: 72-MM-113327 and 31E-MM-108062.
The emails involve Assistant U.S. Attorneys from the Southern District of New York who identify themselves as prosecutors working on the investigation.
The correspondence shows active coordination in July 2019 between the FBI and the U.S. Attorney's Office regarding physical evidence logistics for an investigation.
